Former US presidents, including Carter, Bush, Clinton, and Ford, have united to support a permanent memorial for the victims of the 9/11 attacks.
The memorial board, led by Governor George Pataki, includes notable figures like Robert De Niro and Barbara Walters.
Scheduled to open in 2009, the memorial will feature oak trees, reflecting pools, and a Memorial Hall.
The board aims to raise $500 million for the project.
The new design will preserve the tower remnants, creating a powerful and solemn space for remembrance.
